laboratory_examinations.findings: Enlarged right common iliac, external iliac, and inguinal lymph nodes. The largest node showed increased 18F-FDG avidity.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: On follow-up imaging studies, 3 weeks before this evaluation, the inguinal lymph nodes had decreased in size; the largest node was now 2.0 cm by 0.6 cm and no longer showed increased FDG avidity.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Biopsy specimens reportedly revealed evidence of recurrent ALCL.
